.TH VIJENEX-CIS 1 "December 2024" "1.0.0" "Vijenex CIS Scanner"
.SH NAME
vijenex-cis \- Enterprise Linux Security Compliance Scanner
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vijenex-cis
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Vijenex CIS Scanner is an enterprise-grade security compliance auditing tool for Linux systems based on CIS (Center for Internet Security) benchmarks. Similar to OpenSCAP, it provides automated security compliance scanning with support for multiple Linux distributions.
.PP
The scanner performs automated checks against CIS Benchmarks and generates detailed compliance reports in HTML and CSV formats.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-profile\fR LEVEL
Set CIS profile level (Level1, Level2). Default: Level1
.RS
.IP "Level1"
Basic security requirements with minimal impact on functionality
.IP "Level2"
Enhanced security requirements, may impact functionality
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-output-dir\fR DIR
Output directory for reports. Default: /var/log/vijenex-cis/
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR FORMAT
Report format (html, csv, both). Default: both
.TP
\fB\-\-milestones\fR FILES
Specific milestone files to scan (space-separated)
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR
Show help message and exit
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B sudo vijenex-cis
Run complete CIS compliance scan with default settings
.TP
.B sudo vijenex-cis --profile Level2
Run Level 2 CIS compliance scan
.TP
.B sudo vijenex-cis --output-dir /tmp/security-reports
Run scan with custom output directory
.TP
.B sudo vijenex-cis --format csv --profile Level1
Generate CSV report only for Level 1 profile
.TP
.B sudo vijenex-cis --milestones milestone-1-1.json milestone-1-2.json
Scan specific milestone files only
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/vijenex-cis/
Scanner installation directory with OS-specific scanners
.TP
.I /etc/vijenex-cis/
Configuration directory
.TP
.I /var/log/vijenex-cis/
Default output directory for scan reports
.SH SUPPORTED SYSTEMS
.TP
.B Red Hat Enterprise Linux
RHEL 8, RHEL 9
.TP
.B CentOS
CentOS 7
.TP
.B Ubuntu
Ubuntu 20.04 LTS, 22.04 LTS, 24.04 LTS
.TP
.B Debian
Debian 11
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Scan completed successfully
.TP
.B 1
Error occurred during scan
.SH NOTES
Root privileges are required for complete system scanning. Some checks may fail without root access.
